Amazingly simple. Used Penzey's seafood stock instead of clam juice... ate as a main course with bread to sop up broth. Used a form to keep shrimp mixture and the wow factor is amazing. We had chilled a Crement, such a perfect pair!

Rating: 4
This recipe was unbelievable! It takes a little bit of skill to pull off, but it was totally worth the time/multiple pots. The key to using the full amount of veggies is to cut them into matchsticks and time the cooking of them so that they and the shrimp are definitely still a bit underdone before you ladle the hot soup over them. The shrimp will continue to cook and the veggies will soften slightly, so you have to make sure they are all cooked correctly. I used 1.5 lbs of shrimp and their shells. Awesome.

Rating: 4
I forgot to add that I only included a small zucchini and 1/2 of a large red pepper and included 1.5 lbs of shrimp...also based on other reviewers that the veggies were overpowering. It completely worked...I might add some shallot to it next time.

Rating: 4
I made this for our NYE party, served in small glasses. It was a HUGE hit! Based on other reviewers I added a few dashes of hot sauce to add some spice plus I threw in a couple dashes of ground ginger. Gave it great flavor and it simmered on the stove for about an hour before I served it and I think that helped the flavors meld even more. Will definitely make this again!

