Rating: 3
This soup is rich and special - great first course for a special occasion, and really not that complicated and time consuming when you make the liquid part the day before, reserve the uncooked shrimp meat, then saute it with the zucchini & pepper just before serving. In the future, I plan to use less butter as the soup took on an oily look when I served it. It has enough rich flavor from the madeira to do without all the butter called for.